From 8ae047f02371a66ed01345544e6d61237bd96efb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 16:29:26 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] add an Android app IPC socket

A unix stream socket at $CMUS_ANDROID_SOCKET (unset = disabled) for the
Android wrapper app: pushes newline-delimited JSON events (status,
position, volume, and a full options dump, composed and flushed at most
once per main-loop iteration from the player_info snapshot flags) and
accepts raw cmus command lines like the server.c socket. Single client,
new connection wins, every connect starts with a full snapshot.

Everything is guarded by CONFIG_ANDROID, a plain compile definition the
app build sets; upstream builds never define it and stay unaffected.

